==Polish==
===Etymology===
Note that there is no Polish word ''chlujny''.  ''Niechlujny'' is related to the Russian [[холя]] meaning 'care, attention' and [[холуй]] meaning an 'obsequious over-attentive servant', and also to the Polish [[schludny]] meaning 'neat, tidy'.  [[schludny]] derives from [[chludzić]], 'to clean thoroughly, to have high standards of cleanliness'.  This word derives from the Ancient Greek [[κλύζω]] 'to wash' (cf. [[κλύδων]] 'a wave' and [[कlळोल]]) 

